    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly dice</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, drain your <strong>tofu</strong>, pat dry with kitchen paper and crumble it with your fingers directly into the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the tofu and cook, stirring frequently, for 3-4 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced pepper</strong> with your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to the pan with the diced pepper, then add your<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(save the rest for later!) and the <strong>spinach</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the spinach has wilted and the rice has warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>veg</strong> <strong>fried</strong> <strong>cauliflower</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the spinach is wilting and the cauliflower rice is warming through, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is crisp, add the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> and your <strong>agave </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until the soy sauce has been absorbed \u2013 this is your <strong>scrambled tofu</strong></p><p>Mix <strong>half</strong> the <strong>scrambled tofu </strong>and<strong> half</strong> the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> through the veg fried cauliflower rice (you'll use the rest for garnish!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/scrambled-tofu-and-veg-fried-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>remaining scrambled tofu</strong> over the <strong>veg</strong> <strong>fried cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
